OL,3,CPolitician 'targeted by car' as
OL,4,Cofficials face growing threats
OL,6,FGuernsey's Deputy Carl Meerveld said:
OL,7,F"I've had someone drive their car at
OL,8,Fme and blow their horn as they missed
OL,9,Fme by a few inches, which I had to
OL,10,Freport to the police.
OL,12,F"I believe it was very much
OL,13,Fpolitically motivated."
OL,15,FDeputy Meerveld explained: "I've also
OL,16,Fhad angry people turn up at my door
OL,17,F... I have no problem with people
OL,18,Fbeing angry and wanting to discuss
OL,19,Fissues personal to them, but it isn't
OL,20,Fappropriate to turn up at somebody's
OL,21,Fdoor and shout at them.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G2/8
