OL,3,CPolitician 'targeted by car' as
OL,4,Cofficials face growing threats
OL,6,FSpeaking about the level of abuse
OL,7,Fpoliticians now face, Deputy Louise
OL,8,FDoublet said: "Online abuse is often
OL,9,Fdirected at members who are women,
OL,10,Fmembers of the LGBTQ+ community and
OL,11,Fthose who are different nationalities
OL,12,F- and in the workplace those
OL,13,Fcharacteristics would be protected ...
OL,14,FI think we do need more services to
OL,15,Ftackle this."
OL,17,FDeputy Jonathon Renouf added: "Social
OL,18,Fmedia encourages an aggressive style
OL,19,Fof communication and sometimes that
OL,20,Fsteps over the limit."
